***DDL - Data Definition Language

Data Definition Language (DDL) specifies the database schema. The statements used in DDL are CREATE, ALTER, DROP. DDL statements are typically used to set up and configure a new database before we insert data.

***DML - Data Manipulation Language

Data Manipulation Language (DML) enables users to access or manipulate data. INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT are the statements used in DML.


***DCL - Data Control Language

 Data Control Language (DCL) is used to grant or revoke access control. Its statements are REVOKE and GRANT.


***TCL - Transaction Control Language

Transaction Control Language (TCL) controls the transactions of DML and DDL commands. Its statements are BEGIN and COMMIT.


